-- Mediolanum says Q1 net profit fell 41 pct
-- 
-- Wed May 14, 2014 08:24AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 14 (Reuters) - Italian asset manager Mediolanum <MED.MI> said its net profit in the first quarter dropped 41 percent on lower performance fees and higher IT and marketing costs.

Net profit was 81 million euros ($111 million), while total assets rose 10 percent to 58,9 billion euros, the company said in a statement on Wednesday.